4.19/5  rDev -6.1%look: 3.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4From a 16oz can, dated 11/29/16. Served in a nonic.
Pours a hazy bronze-gold with a meager half-finger of head, gone too fast to really get a good look at, and very little lacing. By the time I get it to the sofa it looks like it was poured yesterday.
Smells of peaches, pears, pineapple and cantaloupe with faint notes of balsam and cookies.
The taste is beautifully bitter with pineapple and papaya, grapefruit pith and seville orange overlaying a crisp sugar cookie body. Finishes with more grapefruit, piney, resinous hop oils on the tongue and a boozy smoldering in the gullet.
Feel is thick and slick, a little soapy, medium-and-a-bit bodied with so-so carbonation and some boozy warmth.
Overall, this is a resinous hop bomb but built over a satisfyingly substantial malt body if a little lifeless in the glass. But, still, a great-big, flavourful AIPA. 864 characterspapposilenus, Dec 28, 2016
