4.24/5  rDev -4.9%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.252016-06-10
16oz can purchased at a Family Thrift Center in Rapid City South Dakota, driven to Denver, and then flown to Chicago. Served in a pint glass. Dated 05/10/16. I drank a lot of this in Rapid City and brought four or five cans home.
Pours clear golden with a slight brassy tinge and a coarse, medium-sized head. Moderate to low carbonation. Smell is terrific, strong clear fresh hops, honeysuckle and flowers.
Taste is a nice blast of piney/grapefruit floral hops with a little tropical hint and a honeysuckle sweetness. Finish is super bitter.
Mouthfeel is resinous and dry. Overall, very good beer. 611 characterssnaotheus, Jun 11, 2016
