4.04/5  rDev -9.4%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4L: Pours a quite murky bright glowing gold with tinges of orange and a mild quickly dissipating head. Tiny specks of yeast sediment held in suspension, with no head retention or lacing to speak of. This beer’s got a very pretty hue, but really could have used more carbonation and foam in the pour.
S: Lots of Mosaic and Citra coming through right off the bat with notes of papaya, mango, ripe apricots, lemons and some candied watermelon. There’s also a decent amount of thick bread crust-like malt.
T: Very approachable with some grass and stonefruit from the hops. Hops are fruity, revealing citrus and mango, but on the whole more grassy than I expected, particularly in the finish. Not as dry as I would imagine, a decent amount of soft bready malt that accentuates the perception of sweet, juicy tree fruits. Finishes semi-dry with bitter lemon rind and a lingering herbaceousness.
F: Medium-plus body with surprisingly little carbonation. A bit lush and silky on the palate.
Thoughts: A pretty solid IPA with a really nice nose, but I didn't find this to be nearly as jaw-dropping as many BA's have led us to believe. Despite employing some of my favorite hop varieties, I found there to be a bit too much grassiness, as well as more malt than I look for an IPA of this strength. 1,294 charactersthepenguin, May 08, 2016
