4.63/5  rDev +3.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.75COD 2/1716.  Copper/orange pour with a touch of haze and garnet.  World class head volume, lacing and retention.
Quite aromatic world class nose of mango, orange, pineapple and a touch of pepper with light pine and rind forming the hop base.  Underneath is a slightly sweet biscuit and caramel malt base.
Medium body with a very smooth texture that is oily and has light creamy aspects.  Superb carbonation with a fair burst of effervescence in the middle and a finely bubbled prickly finish.
The flavor profile is World Class and shows how good an IPA can be.  All the flavors of the nose appear over a slightly sweet malt base that is bready, yet toasted and crisp, coupled with a caramel undertone.  Bitterness is moderate and balance is perfect.  Tropical hop flavors arrive first with orange flowing to pineapple and finishing with mango as the mid-palate sweetness arrives.  The middle produces a moderate rind bitterness with a pine aspect underneath.  Here is where the ride begins.  From the middle on, bitterness rides on a rising wave of sweetness that sees it shift from rind based to pine and ends with a light peppery spruce by the finish.  Underneath the bitterness, mango and passion fruit frolic in the sweet base.  The finish is slightly dry and the combined flavors and bitterness of the finish linger.  This beer takes its competitors to school and is a must try. 1,386 characterstillmac62, Mar 09, 2016
