4.64/5  rDev +4%look: 3.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.75Grabbed a four pack, canned mid February, so pretty dang fresh.  When I got home, I opened this up immediately so not fridge temperature, but not warm.
Look:  The beer pours a hazy orange brown.  Off white head, maybe a finger of head from a somewhat aggressive pour.  Carbonation seems a little low.
Smell:  Holy crapeth, the aromatics are excellent.  Passion fruit initially, pine, and after a swirl of the glass, some mango and other tropical fruits.  One of the best beers I've had, aroma wise.  
Taste:  Taste is pretty close to the nose, there's some passion fruit and tropical fruits throughout, and then I get a little bit more pine near the end.  
Feel:  The carbonation seemed a little low on the beer, but not really awful.  As my can warmed, it seemed a bitterness appeared in the finish.
Overall:  Wow.  I've had Todd on tap several times, and have always loved it, but for some reason this can really did it for me last night.  The can seemed hazier than the tap I've had at Surly.  Seek this beer out if you're into tropical, fruity IPA. 1,057 charactersCfred371, Mar 03, 2016
