4.45/5  rDev -0.2%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Can into a Gandhi-Bot tulip. Thanks, Alex!
A: Deep, hazy orange-gold body under an inch of off-white head. Decent retention, moderate lace. Pretty nice.
S: Intense hoppiness, with lots of pine and grapefruit. Some tropical notes, too, as well as a surprising amount of crystal malt sweetness. Hugely aromatic, and very inviting.
T: Follows the nose: flavor abounds. Fruity hops, resinous hops, caramel malts, everything that you expect to find in a DIPA is here in spades. Citrus, spruce, and malt are all huge presences, but no one element overwhelms the others. Plenty of bitterness on the back end to keep the sweetness in check. Terrific.
M: Medium-to-full bodied, with plenty of carbonation. Works well with the flavors.
O: Excellent beer, much in the vein of the now-old-school DIPAs that turned me into a hophead years ago. Well done, Surly.
Cheers! 862 characterswoosterbill, Dec 27, 2015
