From a 2.5-week-old can, pours a hazy glowing orange with a couple fingers of fluffy white head. Not much lacing. Good bit of fine particulate matter suspended in the beer, and I have no problem with that. Head dies down to almost nothing after a few minutes, and lacing is minimal. Nonetheless, a good-looking beer. 
The moment I popped the top on the can, the room filled with the smell of oranges and pine. Just from popping the top. One of the most deliciously aromatic beers I've ever had. Once in the glass, I also get layers of tangerine, pineapple, peaches and some dank. Underneath is a bit of overripe melon and just a little sweet malt, though the fruits and pine dominate for sure. 
Taste is everything in the smell, and it's awesome. One of the best IPAs I've ever had the pleasure to drink. Feel is perfectly medium, with just the right amount of prickly carbonation. Lingering fruity aftertaste mixed with piney bitterness, though nothing crazy. 
Overall, this is just fantastic. Killer like an insane person with an axe, and not of the guitar variety. 1,088 charactersBeers-es, Dec 14, 2015
