4.23/5  rDev -5.2%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5A: Golden blonde color with an orange hue and moderately carbonated
S: The huge citrus aroma reaches out and grabs your olfactory senses; in particular, there is orange, grapefruit, and a slightly floral aroma. 
T: A full range of citrus hop flavors dazzle the pallet with grapefruit, orange, pineapple, and a layer of floral flavors. And with the hop flavors are strong and present, it has measured dimension that is not overly bitterly. In addition, the hops are supported and somewhat balanced by a a solid malt base. This has a certain sweetness that many other IPAs do not possess. 
M: Solid base malt and moderate carbonation and of course the resin from the hops provide modest mouthfeel.
O: A pleasant delicious and distinctive IPA that is one of my favorites. At 7.3 percent ABV this is not a lightweight session IPA. 826 charactersParnellJoseph1138, Dec 04, 2015
