Smell is glorious. Some non-pithy citrus. A bit of pine and malt comes through as well.
Taste is even better than the aroma. Citrus hops meets hints of tropical pineapple. But there is an earthy hop bite also that dances gracefully with a solid malt backbone.
Finish is full enough to be totally respected and loved.
