4.46/5  rDev 0%look: 3.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Three month old can, kept well.
Look:  Amber and orange body that you can see shadows through.  White head.  Slippery lacing as I move the beer around in the glass.  There is no lacing left behind as the beer disappears from the glass.
Smell:  Top of the line.  Rich overripe tropical fruit, sharper pine, and more overripe pineapple.  The aroma is strong and heavy.  The finish is longer and almost clean.  What is left in your chomper and on your tongue is desirable.      
Taste:  The majority of this beer is described above.  Tropical fruit is big in the taste, dominated by pineapple.      
Feel:  Medium base.  Medium low carbonation.  Thick lather in the mouth, some of the thickest I have had in an IPA, not the thickest, but one of the thickest.  Resinous and you could call it tacky on the tongue.
Overall -  This beer is delicious and drinks well, it has a big bold taste.  It tastes like a double but, has the ABV of a single.  Bravo.  
I am sure a fresh can will boost the score.  Someone send me one... 1,020 charactersmabermud, Nov 05, 2015
