4.3/5  rDev -3.6%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4.5Can dated 8/4/2015:
So this is almost 3 months old, so take that into account with this rating, although it is still pretty damn good at this age, so I don't think I'll be pulling down the rating with this review.
It's a fairly cloudy orange-yellow leaning toward the pale side.  Head doesn't build too much at this point, but does linger on the surface and at the edges.
Nose is an alcohol or spruce laced fruit basket.  I get the impression of tropical fruit, some sweet melon notes, and definitely some grapefruit rind.  I also get piney hints behind it all.
Opening seems a little melon combined with grapefruit pith.  There is a sweetness to this that has a hint of alcohol to it, and is perhaps a sign of age; muted sweet fruit notes (tropical, I think) are there as well, but also have likely faded due to age.  By mid taste, the bitter pine and tingling spice notes have taken control of the taste, though there is a lingering honey sweetness that keeps them from overwhelming the palate.
At this point, its a bit of a heavier feeling brew, and the flavors paint my tongue with a stickiness that almost forms a film on it.
I am pretty sure I would have really enjoyed this fresh.  I enjoyed it quite well with 3 months on it, and there are some aspects that seem to me they could be from age (based on other experiences).  Given the other reviews, I'm willing have faith that it would be even better fresh. 1,419 characterscjgiant, Oct 30, 2015
