4.09/5  rDev -8.3%look: 3.75 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4Pint can into my Duvel tulip.
A:  Pours a pretty vibrant, slightly hazy copper with 1" foamy white head that lingers at first, then dissipates quickly.  Retention is above-average, lacing is so-so.
S:  Amazing - huge notes of honeyed citrus, pine & lemongrass.  Caramel & almost a lemon-drop candy note come into focus as well.  Exquisite.
T:  Comes on with flat out lemon/lime, very assertive leading into the mid palate which begins to show more depth.  Initial graham-cracker malt helps to temper the citrus, which then leads to a caramel/honey sweetness that is trying in vain to compete with a sudden blistering bitterness.  This mid palate is truly something special - there's an elasticity to the flavors here that I just haven't seen before.  The finish is bitter as well, although it diminishes smoothly into a mellow doughy malt note tempered once again by citrus.
M:  Moderate-to-slightly high carb married to a fairly full, supportive malt frame.  It's just a little bit soapy & finishes surprisingly crisp.  Well above-average.
O:  This is one of the more well-thought-out & generally impressive IPAs to have passed my lips. 1,142 charactersMUTINY, Oct 12, 2015
