4.35/5  rDev -2.5%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.25Awesome can art. Pours a very murky orange with a moderate white foam head that quickly recedes. Leaves a thin ring of lacing around the edge and a very thin layer at the surface.
Aroma is exploding with tropical fruits and citrusy hops. Intense mango, grapefruit and pineapple. 
Taste is dominated by hops and a strong bitterness. Pine takes a stronger hold than in the aroma, and the tropical flavors take more of a backseat (although its still strong). Orange comes on strong as it warms, joined by some nice, grassy floral notes. Hops fade considerably as it warms, allowing the tropical notes into the spotlight, where they do well paired with a bitter finish. 
Mouthfeel is light bodied and an easy drinker for a hoppy, bitter IPA checking in at 7.2%. Could easily down this entire 4-pack, possibly even two of them. Finishes dry.
Having the taste of Pseudo Sue relatively fresh in my mind probably hurt this one, but still an excellent IPA. Looking forward to the rest of the 4 pack, as I'm thinking my view will only improve. 1,037 charactersmajorbase2, Oct 07, 2015
