A: Moderate pour yields 3/4 finger white head which quickly becomes lace.  Hazy brass-colored liquid.  Lots of little floaties, so this could be evidence of copious dry hopping.
S: Deep wafts of mango and pineapple during the pour!  Orange, delicate and clean malt.  Dank, deep prickly evergreen.
T: Ruby red grapefruit juice, mango, slight rustic bread.
M: Dry, citrus pith bitterness.  Grat biter dry finish, but not a tongue buckler.
