4.51/5  rDev +1.1%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5A: Moderate murk in this orange-bronze beer, sprite bubbles rise through the suspended sediment. I hate sediment. Head doesn't last, I wonder how intense this is really going to be if it can't maintain a billow. I also wish the description was more offense, a la Arrogant Bastard. If they are going to threaten to shred my face and use all the cliche aggressive adjectives, I feel like they should put an outright "Fuck You" somewhere in there too. Get some balls.
S: The nose has got it all. Citrus, floral, earth, pine. Nearly the full range of what hops have to offer. Slight sourdough malt, bitter. Fantastic.
T: Also great. Not as emotive of flavors as the nose had, but still robust. Orange juice and peel, pine, vegetal, some good spice like rye, also very, very bitter. Malts keep it palatable, but never really show their face directly. Pulpy woody pine on the finish, observable upon retro-olfaction long after the last sip.
M: Medium-full body, nicely thick for an IPA. Carbonation makes it lively, but not biting.
O: Despite being neither intimidated nor offended by the label, this was still a great experience. Great variety of hop flavors, intensely bitter, but somehow not too off-balanced. A nuanced, complex, encompassing, structurally sound hop bomb. Expensive, but definitely worth a one-time purchase. 1,326 characters1000lbgrizzly, Sep 05, 2015
