3.97/5  rDev -11%look: 3.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 3.75Pint-sized can - canned on 7/11/15 (stamped on bottom) - Poured into a tulip glass, as suggested:
Pours hazed deep golden amber with a thin white head. Spots of lacing stick.
The smell is of very intense citrus.
The taste is of boozed-soaked citrus (especially grapefruit) with a bit of caramelized malt. It has a perfumy/grapefruity aftertaste lingers.
It is full-bodied. Somewhat astringent. Raw alcohol lingers on the palate.
Almost too intense, it is a "sipper". Good for a boozy hop fix. Don't know that I'm impressed enough to think that it is worth the 5.25 a single / about 18 a four-pack. 602 charactersjwc215, Aug 29, 2015
