4.91/5  rDev +10.1%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.7516oz can.  7/16/15 canning date.
It pours a hazy but pretty orange color with a 2 finger head that fades rather quickly.  The nose is very strong and very dank.  This might be the most dank beer I have poured.  Also strong citrus with this.  
The taste is strong citra and mosaic hops dankness.  That is the primary mover of this beer.   Juicy citrus also makes an appearance.  There is a nice blend of bitterness and sweetness as well.  The 7.2% ABV is invisible.  Very well hidden. 
Some have had cans where the carbonation was a little weak.  My 7/16 canning was too.  Other canning dates have had no carbonation issues.  Poor lacing, but who cares?!
This is a fantastic beer worthy of the ratings you see.  It is a bit spendy, but worth the price.  My face is shredded.  Glad I have more of this waiting for me.  
Can did have the date canned. 852 charactersBeer-vortex, Aug 21, 2015
