This one pours a golden orange, with a off-white head, about one inch, and lots of lacing.
This one smells awesome, dankly citrusy, lots of grapefruit orange, orange peel, and pineapple. Smells so inviting and bangin'.
Unsurprisingly, this also tastes quite good. So much tropical and citrus character, fruits galore, with a dank character underpinning everything here, grassy and pine, with a really bitter and awesome finish. It's so easy to just gulp this down, it's so delicious.
This one has a very crisp and juicy mouthfeel, full, but not thick or syrupy at all, with a moderate level of carbonation.
One of the better IPAs I've ever had, a really excellent beer here. 711 charactersGreesyFizeek, Aug 14, 2015
