4.74/5  rDev +6.3%look: 4 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Aroma is a wonderful mix of pineapple, blueberries, honey, and wild onion. Some piney quality as well. Fresh and floral with some grassy notes. Very strong and pungent. Funky passion fruity, mandarins. Very difficult to smell anything past the hops. Clean yeast and malt, malt perhaps supplying a bit of a honey note. Maybe some toasted bread is there as well.
Pours slightly murky light orange with a small off-white head. Ok lacing, with moderate head retention.
Big tropical fruit and citrus on the palate. Again wild onion, garlic, and blueberry characteristic of Mosaic in my experience. Some honey is notable too. Orange and mango with a hint of biscuit. Grass, kumquats. Big flavor without being heavy on the palate. Dry finish with lingering resiny hops and honey. 
Medium low carbonation with medium body. Mouth filling hop flavor with little bitterness in comparison. Almost refreshing.
Quite the beer. Crazy complex hop character. I could see people saying things like hops this interesting could mask flaws, but that seems untrue as I've recently had an all Mosaic beer that had interesting hop flavor, but drinkability was marred by yeast esters and under attenuation. This beer is clean and bone dry allowing the hop flavors to really come out without being too sticky or bitter. 1,297 characterssjccmd, Aug 10, 2015
