Pours a deep, golden orange color. Very hazy. Large , thick, soapy white head that results in a quarter thick ring. 
Smells of malts, ripe citrus, and mosaic hops. Pretty dank and funky. 
The citra hops are on full display here. It comes off the top ropes with a blast of orange. Tastes like I just ate a juciy clementine, rind and all. A little bit of peach juice, some sweet malts, and then some bitterness that just seems to snowball all the way till the end. Very clean finish. 
Pretty full bodied beer here with significant resin feel. 
