4.17/5  rDev -6.5%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4On-tap at the new brewery restaurant (my first visit). Tasted 21 April 2015.
Pours hazy bright golden-orange. One finger of white head, excellent retention and lacing.
Smell is incredibly fruity, bursting with big citra hops. Remind me of TG's PseudoSue. Oranges, pineapple, mango. Full underneath that with sweet caramel malts.
Taste is really good, but those amazing aromatic hops are beaten down by a powerful bitterness. I get them for a second, then they're going down as the bitter rises, the two crossing paths.
Feel is decent. A little flat, a little heavy. But good and bright.
Excellent beer, super aromatic in the nose, and delightfully fruity. 660 characterszeledonia, Jun 03, 2015
