4.62/5  rDev +3.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5On tap into a 10 oz Surly snifter at the new brew hall.
A: bright shiny golden pear, a little bit hazy, a 1 finger head that sticks around.
S:  Ambrosia.  I think it's the best bouquet I've encountered on a beer.  White grapes, blueberries, apricot, and also some light mango, passion fruit, and pineapple...not the dank juiciness of Abrasive, say...sweeter and lighter (but not too much).  Some bright flowers.  Also some crackery malt.  And maybe something interesting from the yeast. The nose doesn't knock you over, but it draws you in; close to perfect.  
T: More aggressive than the nose and not quite as subtle, but still good complexity and very delicious.  The citra combination of pine and citrus comes out more strongly on the back end (and the more I sip).
M: good body, medium carbonation, surprisingly creamy, moderately dry finish, hops bring some tingly sensations to the tongue. 
Overall:  Excellent 918 charactersTaybeh, Feb 04, 2015
