4.46/5  rDev 0%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.512 oz draft served in a small goblet.
High clarity golden orange with a thin layer of white foam that sticks around the edges nicely, forming an unbroken collar. Drippy lace forms as the glass is sipped. 
Very pungent tropical aroma, mango and dried pineapple, nectarine.
Definitely a big west coast vibe already.
Taste is packed with tropical hop fruitiness, more mango and pineapple from the Citra and Mosaic, with a light undercurrent of clean crackery malt underneath. Moderate bitterness, though perfectly balanced and very drinkable. Light to medium bodied with little to no residual sugars. Highly sessionable. 
A comment was made that "Surly made a Half Acre beer", then the bartender came by and said the exact same thing. 734 charactersemerge077, Dec 04, 2014
4.8/5  rDev +7.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4.75canned 8.6.15. re-reviewed about two weeks after can date.
haven't reviewed in a long time, but compelled to review this one. fwiw if i had the time i'd go back and lower a lot of my old ratings. currently my favorite beer ever.
oddly i liked this much better out of the can than when i had it on tap.
no carb issues. explosive citra and mosaic aroma, like smelling a bowl of pellets. dank and fruity. flavor is the same juicy hops and a restrained bitterness. overall a phenomenal beer and i hope it's canned from time to time. a game changer for me, if i have access to this i'll pass on trading for HT and sue.
*update: undercarbed. head dissipates quickly. fine dark sediment on the bottom of the cans after a few weeks. 724 charactersMrMcGibblets, Dec 03, 2014
